HIV/AIDS: Kasar Sin ta Bayyana Ƙaruwar Sabbin Cutar HIV da kashi 14%
Kasar Sin ta ba da rahoton karuwar kashi 14 cikin dari na yawan 'yan kasar da ke dauke da cutar kanjamau da kanjamau.
A cikin ƙasar, an ƙidaya mutane fiye da 820,000 da cutar ta shafa.
A cikin kwata na biyu na 2018, an samu sabbin mutane kusan 40,000.
Yawancin sabbin cututtukan sun kasance ta hanyar jima'i, wanda ya nuna canji daga baya.
A al'adance, cutar HIV tana yaduwa ne ta hanyar jini da aka yi wa wasu mutane a wasu sassan kasar Sin.
Amma adadin mutanen da suka kamu da cutar ta wannan hanyar ya ragu zuwa kusan babu, in ji likitocin kasar Sin a wani taro a lardin Yunnan.
Yawan mutanen da ke dauke da cutar kanjamau da kanjamau a kasar Sin ya karu da mutane 100,000 a kowace shekara.
Yaduwar cutar kanjamau ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce a cikin al'ummar LGBT na kasar Sin.
An haramta luwadi a kasar Sin a shekarar 1997, amma ana zargin cewa nuna bambanci ga LGBT na ci gaba.
Saboda tsattsauran ra'ayin kasar, bincike ya nuna cewa kashi 70 zuwa 90 cikin dari na maza da ke yin jima'i da maza za su auri mata.
Yawancin cututtuka suna zuwa ne daga rashin kariya ta jima'i a lokacin wannan jima'i.
Tun daga 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin samar da maganin cutar HIV ga kowa a kasar a matsayin wani bangare na kokarin magance matsalar.
